<br>
You're riding the subway minding your own business.  Some guy sits down across from you and starts looking at you, your hair, your shirt, your pants to see if it's got a zipper or button fly, what kind of shoes you're wearing, takes note of the belly button ring you may or may not have...<br>
<br>
A bit creepy.  Imagine each detail as <br>
a) the next inspect click from the same person, or<br>
b) the next tick of time the persons stays next to you after inspecting you.<br>
<br>
<br>
Avalis.<br>
<br>
I feel a bit that way when I see it.  So I turned it off, knowing that many people don't see it that way.<br>
<br>
